---
title: Date picker
---
p.-text
  | Use the function <code>chi.datepicker(elem)</code> to instantiate a new date picker component in the input of type
  | text element passed as a parameter. This component uses the
  | <a href="https://github.com/iamkun/dayjs">Day.js library</a>.
p.-text
  | Input of type text should be used and any other type, including type date, will be converted into type text.

h2 Base
.example.-mb--3
  .-p--3
    .m-form__item
      label(class="a-label", for="datepicker-1") Date
      .m-input__wrapper.-icon--right(style="width:14rem;")
        input#datepicker-1.a-input(type="text", placeholder="MM/DD/YYYY", value="")
        .a-icon.-text--muted
          svg
            use(xlink:href='#icon-date')
  :code(lang="html",style="height:20rem")
    <div class="m-form__item">
      <label class="a-label" for="datepicker-1">Date</label>
      <div class="m-input__wrapper -icon--right">
        <input id="datepicker-1" type="text" class="a-input" placeholder="MM/DD/YYYY" value="">
        <div class="a-icon -text--muted">
          <svg>
            <use xlink:href="#icon-date"></use>
          </svg>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <script>chi.datePicker(document.getElementById('datepicker-1'));</script>

